What is a disk image?
	A disk image is virtual/software based representation of an actual disk, allowing an OS or an FS to be manipulated and used without need of a physical disk.
What is the command to make a disk image?
	dd if=/dev/zero whatever of=/mnt/name.img
What is a disk partition?
	A disk partition is a sliced section of a hard disk which can be used as a secondary storage.

